---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Zelify Docs | Zelify">
  <main class="container mx-auto px-4 py-16">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-center mb-4">Zelify Docs</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-600 text-center mb-12 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
      Comprehensive documentation about our policies, terms, and data protection measures.
    </p>

    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <div class="mb-4 border-b border-gray-200">
        <ul class="flex flex-wrap -mb-px text-sm font-medium text-center" id="docTabs" role="tablist">
          <li class="mr-2" role="presentation">
            <button class="inline-block p-4 border-b-2 rounded-t-lg hover:text-gray-600 hover:border-gray-300 dark:hover:text-gray-300 tab-button active" id="privacy-tab" data-target="privacy">Privacy Policy</button>
          </li>
          <li class="mr-2" role="presentation">
            <button class="inline-block p-4 border-b-2 rounded-t-lg hover:text-gray-600 hover:border-gray-300 dark:hover:text-gray-300 tab-button" id="terms-tab" data-target="terms">Terms of Use</button>
          </li>
          <li role="presentation">
            <button class="inline-block p-4 border-b-2 rounded-t-lg hover:text-gray-600 hover:border-gray-300 dark:hover:text-gray-300 tab-button" id="data-tab" data-target="data">Data Protection</button>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div id="tabContent" class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-sm border border-gray-100">
        <div class="tab-panel active p-8" id="privacy">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Privacy Policy</h2>
          <div class="prose max-w-none">
            <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">Last updated: January 1, 2024</p>

            <section class="mb-8">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">1. Information We Collect</h3>
              <p class="mb-4">We collect several different types of information for various purposes to provide and improve our service to you:</p>
              
              <h4 class="font-semibold mb-2">1.1 Personal Data</h4>
              <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4">
                <li>Identity Information (name, date of birth, government ID)</li>
                <li>Contact Information (email address, phone number, address)</li>
                <li>Financial Information (bank account details, transaction history)</li>
                <li>Technical Data (IP address, browser type, device information)</li>
              </ul>

              <h4 class="font-semibold mb-2">1.2 Usage Data</h4>
              <p>We collect information on how you use our services, including:</p>
              <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4">
                <li>Transaction patterns and frequency</li>
                <li>Features and pages accessed</li>
                <li>Time spent on platform</li>
                <li>Technical interaction details</li>
              </ul>
            </section>

            <section class="mb-8">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">2. How We Use Your Information</h3>
              <p class="mb-4">Your information is used for the following purposes:</p>
              <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4">
                <li>Processing your transactions and maintaining your account</li>
                <li>Verifying your identity and preventing fraud</li>
                <li>Improving our services and user experience</li>
                <li>Communicating with you about your account and our services</li>
                <li>Complying with legal and regulatory requirements</li>
              </ul>
            </section>

            <section class="mb-8">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">3. Legacy System Integration</h3>
              <div class="space-y-4">
                <h4 class="font-semibold mb-2">3.1 Core Banking Integration</h4>
                <p>Our platform interfaces with multiple legacy banking systems through:</p>
                <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4">
                  <li>ISO 8583 message protocol for financial transactions</li>
                  <li>SWIFT MT103 format for international transfers</li>
                  <li>FIX protocol for real-time market data</li>
                  <li>AS2 protocol for secure file transfers</li>
                </ul>
                
                <h4 class="font-semibold mb-2">3.2 Data Retention Compliance</h4>
                <p>We maintain historical data in accordance with:</p>
                <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4">
                  <li>Basel III requirements for transaction records</li>
                  <li>PSD2 compliance for payment services</li>
                  <li>SOX requirements for audit trails</li>
                  <li>FATCA reporting requirements</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </section>

            <section class="mb-8">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">4. Technical Infrastructure</h3>
              <div class="space-y-4">
                <h4 class="font-semibold mb-2">4.1 System Architecture</h4>
                <p>Our platform utilizes a hybrid architecture combining:</p>
                <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4">
                  <li>Mainframe systems for core banking operations</li>
                  <li>Microservices for modern API interfaces</li>
                  <li>Event-driven architecture for real-time processing</li>
                  <li>Blockchain integration for selected transactions</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </section>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="tab-panel hidden p-8" id="terms">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Terms of Use</h2>
          <div class="prose max-w-none">
            <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">Last updated: January 1, 2024</p>

            <section class="mb-8">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">1. Account Terms</h3>
              <div class="space-y-4">
                <p>By creating an account on Zelify, you agree to the following terms:</p>
                <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
                  <li>You must be 18 years or older to use our services</li>
                  <li>You must provide accurate and complete information</li>
                  <li>You are responsible for maintaining account security</li>
                  <li>You must comply with all applicable laws and regulations</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </section>

            <section class="mb-8">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">2. Service Terms</h3>
              <div class="space-y-4">
                <h4 class="font-semibold">2.1 Transaction Processing</h4>
                <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
                  <li>All transactions are subject to verification and approval</li>
                  <li>We may decline transactions that appear suspicious</li>
                  <li>Transaction limits may apply based on account status</li>
                  <li>Fees and exchange rates are subject to change</li>
                </ul>

                <h4 class="font-semibold mt-4">2.2 Account Security</h4>
                <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
                  <li>You must keep your login credentials confidential</li>
                  <li>You must enable two-factor authentication</li>
                  <li>Report any unauthorized access immediately</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </section>

            <section class="mb-8">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">3. Regulatory Compliance</h3>
              <div class="space-y-4">
                <h4 class="font-semibold">3.1 Banking Regulations</h4>
                <p>Our services comply with multiple regulatory frameworks:</p>
                <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
                  <li>Federal Reserve Regulation E for electronic transfers</li>
                  <li>OFAC compliance for international transactions</li>
                  <li>Bank Secrecy Act (BSA) requirements</li>
                  <li>Anti-Money Laundering (AML) provisions</li>
                  <li>Know Your Customer (KYC) protocols</li>
                </ul>

                <h4 class="font-semibold mt-4">3.2 International Standards</h4>
                <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
                  <li>SEPA compliance for European transfers</li>
                  <li>Regulation Systems Compliance and Integrity (Reg SCI)</li>
                  <li>International Financial Reporting Standards (IFRS)</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </section>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="tab-panel hidden p-8" id="data">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Data Protection</h2>
          <div class="prose max-w-none">
            <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">Last updated: January 1, 2024</p>

            <section class="mb-8">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">1. Security Measures</h3>
              <div class="space-y-4">
                <h4 class="font-semibold">1.1 Technical Security</h4>
                <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
                  <li>256-bit SSL encryption for all data transmission</li>
                  <li>Multi-layer firewalls and intrusion detection</li>
                  <li>Regular security audits and penetration testing</li>
                  <li>Real-time fraud monitoring systems</li>
                </ul>

                <h4 class="font-semibold mt-4">1.2 Operational Security</h4>
                <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
                  <li>Regular employee security training</li>
                  <li>Strict access control policies</li>
                  <li>24/7 security monitoring</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </section>

            <section class="mb-8">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">2. Data Processing</h3>
              <div class="space-y-4">
                <p>We process your data in accordance with GDPR and other applicable regulations:</p>
                <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
                  <li>Data minimization principles</li>
                  <li>Regular data protection impact assessments</li>
                  <li>Strict data retention policies</li>
                  <li>Third-party vendor security assessments</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </section>

            <section class="mb-8">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">3. Legacy System Security</h3>
              <div class="space-y-4">
                <h4 class="font-semibold">3.1 Mainframe Security</h4>
                <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
                  <li>RACF (Resource Access Control Facility) implementation</li>
                  <li>ACF2 security system integration</li>
                  <li>Top Secret Security system protocols</li>
                  <li>JES2 spool protection measures</li>
                </ul>

                <h4 class="font-semibold mt-4">3.2 Data Encryption Standards</h4>
                <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
                  <li>Triple DES for legacy system compatibility</li>
                  <li>AES-256 for modern system integration</li>
                  <li>HSM (Hardware Security Module) implementation</li>
                  <li>PKI infrastructure for digital signatures</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </section>

            <section class="mb-8">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">4. Compliance Frameworks</h3>
              <div class="space-y-4">
                <h4 class="font-semibold">4.1 Financial Industry Standards</h4>
                <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
                  <li>PCI DSS Level 1 compliance</li>
                  <li>SOC 1 Type II and SOC 2 Type II certifications</li>
                  <li>ISO 27001:2013 certification</li>
                  <li>NIST Cybersecurity Framework implementation</li>
                </ul>

                <h4 class="font-semibold mt-4">4.2 Audit Requirements</h4>
                <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
                  <li>COBIT framework implementation</li>
                  <li>ITIL service management practices</li>
                  <li>Regular penetration testing and vulnerability assessments</li>
                  <li>Continuous compliance monitoring</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </section>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>

<script>
  const tabButtons = document.querySelectorAll('.tab-button');
  const tabPanels = document.querySelectorAll('.tab-panel');

  tabButtons.forEach(button => {
    button.addEventListener('click', () => {
      // Remove active class from all buttons and panels
      tabButtons.forEach(btn => btn.classList.remove('active'));
      tabPanels.forEach(panel => panel.classList.add('hidden'));

      // Add active class to clicked button and show corresponding panel
      button.classList.add('active');
      const targetPanel = document.getElementById(button.dataset.target);
      targetPanel.classList.remove('hidden');
    });
  });
</script>

<style>
  .tab-button.active {
    @apply text-blue-600 border-blue-600;
  }
  .tab-panel {
    @apply p-4;
  }
</style> 